  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span arial=&quot;&quot;&gt;By reasons of size, scale and design the proposed development would akin more to a bed in a shed at odds with the character of the main dwellinghouse and wider area,&amp;nbsp;presenting poor quality accommodation especially when taking into consideration&amp;nbsp;the impacts of the &amp;nbsp;insufficient number of well-located, openable windows which would result in&amp;nbsp;poor natural ventilation and light penetration. Furthermore, the proposal&amp;nbsp;fails to present sufficient details/evidence demonstrating the use/users of the building and fails to plausibly demonstrate the&amp;nbsp;ancillary function of the annexe, which is exacerbated by the size and scale of the proposal.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As such, the proposed development is considered unacceptable and contrary to:-National Planning Policy Framework (MHCLG, February 2019)Policies D4 and D6 of the London Plan (March 2021)Policies CP3 of the Core Strategy (July 2010)Policies BP11 of the&amp;nbsp;Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)Policies SP2, SP4, DMD1 and DMD6 of&amp;nbsp;Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version, December 2021)Residential Extensions and Alterations (SPD) (February 2012)"
